ler)|Carmella]] (with [[Lana (wrestler)|Lana]] and [[Tamina Snuka|Tamina]]) and [[Ruby Riott]] (with [[Liv Morgan]] and [[Sarah Logan]])\n|stip2 = [[Triple threat match]]\n|time2 = 10:08\n\n|match3 = [[The New Day (professional wrestling)|The New Day]] ([[Big E (wrestler)|Big E]] and [[Xavier Woods]]) (with [[Kofi Kingston]]) and [[The Usos]] ([[Jey Uso]] and [[Jimmy Uso]]) defeated [[Chad Gable]] and [[Shelton Benjamin]], and Rusev Day ([[Aiden English]] and [[Rusev (wrestler)|Rusev]])\n|stip3 = [[Eight-man tag team match]]\n|time3 = 8:06\n\n|match4 = Absolution ([[Paige (wrestler)|Paige]], [[Mandy Rose]] and [[Sonya Deville]]) defeated [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]], [[Mickie James]], and [[Sasha Banks]]\n|stip4 = [[Six-woman tag team match]]\n|time4 = 10:07\n\n|match5 = [[AJ Styles]], [[Randy Orton]] and [[Shinsuke Nakamura]] defeated [[Jinder Mahal]], [[Kevin Owens and Sami Zayn]]\n|stip5 = [[Six-man tag team match]]\n|time5 = 10:21\n}}\n\n===2018===\nThe 2018 edition of the special was taped on December 4 at the [[Fort Hood]] in [[Killeen, Texas]]. It aired on December 20 on the [[USA Network]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/article/wwe-tribute-to-the-troops-2018-announcement|title=The 16th Annual WWE Tribute to the Troops will be held Tuesday, Dec. 4, at Fort Hood, Texas|publisher=WWE|date=November 30, 2018|accessdate=November 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/119709-notes-from-2018-wwe-tribute-to-the-troops-taping|title=Notes from the 2018 WWE Tribute to the Troops taping in Fort Hood on Tuesday|publisher=WrestleView|date=December 4, 2018|accessdate=December 10, 2019}}</ref>\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|hide = all\n|results = \n|times  = \n\n|match1 = [[Natalya Neidhart|Natalya]] and [[Ronda Rousey]] defeated The Riott Squad ([[Liv Morgan]] and [[Sarah Logan]]) (with [[Ruby Riott]]), and [[Nia Jax]] and [[Tamina Snuka|Tamina]] by submission \n|stip1  = [[Triple threat tag team match]]\n|time1  = 6:35\n\n|match