efeated [[Chris Jericho]]<ref group=Note>Despite John Cena defending his WWE title against Chris Jericho at the event, at the time it aired, [[Sheamus]] had already won Cena's title at [[TLC: Tables, Ladders and Chairs (2009)|TLC]].</ref>\n|stip3 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]] for the [[WWE Championship]]\n|time3 = 7:53\n}}\n<references group=Note/>\n\n=== 2010 ===\nThe 2010 edition of the special was taped on December 11 in [[Fort Hood, Texas]]. This was the first Tribute to the Troops event not to be held in Iraq or Afghanistan. [[Sean Combs|Diddy]], [[Sherri Shepherd]], [[Miss USA]] [[Rima Fakih]], [[Trace Adkins]] and [[Cedric the Entertainer]] appeared as celebrity guests. ''[[Modern Family]]'' cast member [[Ariel Winter]] sang ''[[The Star-Spangled Banner]]'' (though the performance did not air). Two versions of the program aired: a 60-minute version on December 18, 2010 on NBC and a 2-hour version on December 22, 2010 on USA Network. The NBC broadcast only included the tag team and 6-man tag team matches listed below.\n\n{{Professional wrestling results table\n|results = \n|times = \n|hide = all\n\n|match1 = [[Mark Henry]] won by last  eliminating [[Sheamus]].<ref group=Note>The other participants were:  [[Chavo Guerrero]], [[Chris Masters]], [[Cody Rhodes]], [[Daniel Bryan]],  [[David Otunga]], [[Ezekiel Jackson]], [[Heath Slater]], [[Husky Harris]],  [[John Morrison (wrestler)|John Morrison]], [[Justin Gabriel]], [[Michael  McGillicutty]], [[Santino Marella]] and [[Vladimir Kozlov]].</ref>\n|stip1 = 15-man [[Battle royal  (professional wrestling)|battle royal]]\n|time1 = \n\n|match2 = [[Big Show]] and [[Kofi  Kingston]] defeated [[Dolph Ziggler]] and [[Jack Swagger]]\n|stip2 = [[Tag team match]]\n|time2 = \n\n|match3 = [[R-Truth]] (with [[Eve  Torres]]) defeated [[Ted DiBiase Jr.|Ted DiBiase]] (with [[Maryse  Ouellet|Maryse]])\n|stip3 = [[Singles match (professional  wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time3 = \n\n|match4 = [[Kelly Kelly]], [[Natalya  Neidhart|Natalya]] and [[The Bella Twins]] ([[Brie Bella]] and [[Nikki  Bella]]) defeated [[Melina Perez|Melina]], [[Alicia Fox]] and [[LayCool]]  ([[Layla El|Layla]] and [[Michelle McCool]])\n|stip4 = Eight-Diva Santa's Little Helper [[tag team match]]\n|time4 = \n\n|match5 = [[John Cena]], [[Rey Mysterio]]  and [[Randy Orton]] defeated [[Alberto Del Rio]], [[Wade Barrett]] and [[The  Miz]] (with [[Alex Riley]])\n|stip5 = [[Six-man tag team match]]\n|time5 = \n\n}}\n<references group=Note/>\n\n=== 2011 ===\nOn December 1, 2011, NBC and WWE announced the 2011 edition of ''WWE Tribute to the Troops'' would air December 17, 2011 on NBC.<ref name=\"tribute2011\">{{cite web|url=http://tv.ign.com/articles/121/1213740p1.html|title=WWE Tribute to the Troops Date Revealed|publisher=IGN|accessdate=2011-12-01|date=December 1, 2011}}</ref> On the December 5 edition of ''Raw'', it was also announced the show would also air on the USA Network on December 13, 2011. The December 13 broadcast included all 7 matches, which the December 17 version included only the first and last match. The event was taped December 11, 2011 in [[Fayetteville, North Carolina]] at the [[Cumberland County Crown Coliseum|Crown Coliseum]] (though WWE said on-air that they were actually at [[Fort Bragg]]), the taping was performed in front of U.S. military service members from the nearby Fort Bragg military base and their families.<ref name=\"2011taping\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/WWE_News_3/article_55901.shtml|title=WWE News: Tribute to the Troops taping Sunday - who's advertised, celebrity scheduled for match|author=James Caldwell|publisher=[[PWTorch]]|date=2011-12-11|accessdate=2011-12-12}}</ref> This is also the first Tribute to the Troops that was taped indoors rather than outdoors. [[Lilian Garcia]]'s performance of ''The Star-Spangled Banner'' was edited out of the USA Network broadcast.\n\nThe event featured a pre-recorded message from President [[Barack Obama]]. [[Nickelback]] performed the [[Radio edit|clean version]] of \"[[Burn It to the Ground]]\", the theme song of ''Raw'', and \"[[When We Stand Together]]\". [[Sgt. Slaughter]] made a special appearance, supporting [[Zack Ryder]] ringside. [[Maria Menounos]] also made a special guest appearance, teaming with [[Kelly Kelly]], [[Eve Torres]] and [[Alicia Fox]] to defeat [[The Divas of Doom]] ([[Beth Phoenix]] and [[Natalya Neidhart|Natalya]]) and [[The Bella Twins]] ([[Brie Bella]] and [[Nikki Bella]]) in an Eight-Diva tag team match, in which she pinned down Phoenix for the victory. George Wallace performed some [[stand-up comedy]]. [[Mary J. Blige]] performed \"[[My Life II... The Journey Continues (Act 1)|Need Someone]]\" and \"[[Family Affair (Mary J. Blige song)|Family Affair]]\".\n\n{{Professional wrestling results table\n|results = \n|times = \n|hide = all\n\n|match1 = [[Randy Orton]] vs. [[Wade  Barrett]] ended in a [[double countout]]\n|stip1 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time1 = \n\n|match2 = [[Zack Ryder]] (with [[Sgt.  Slaughter]]) defeated [[Jack Swagger]] (with [[Dolph Ziggler]])\n|stip2 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time2 = \n\n|match3 = [[Kelly Kelly]], [[Eve  Torres]], [[Alicia Fox]] and [[Maria Menounos]] defeated [[The Divas of  Doom]] ([[Beth Phoenix]] and [[Natalya Neidhart|Natalya]]) and [[The Bella  Twins]] ([[Brie Bella]] and [[Nikki Bella]])\n|stip3 = [[Eight-woman tag team match|Eight-Diva tag team match]]\n|time3 = \n\n|match4 = [[Daniel Bryan]] defeated  [[Cody Rhodes]]\n|stip4 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time4 = \n\n|match5 = [[Primo and Epico]] (with  [[Rosa Mendes]]) defeated Air Boom ([[Evan Bourne]] and [[Kofi Kingston]])\n|stip5 = [[Tag team match]]\n|time5 = \n\n|match6 = [[Sheamus]] defeated [[Drew  McIntyre]]\n|stip6 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time6 = \n\n|match7 = [[John Cena]], [[Big Show]] and  [[CM Punk]] defeated [[Mark Henry]], [[The Miz]] and [[Alberto Del Rio]]  (with [[Ricardo Rodriguez (wrestler)|Ricardo Rodriguez]])\n|stip7 = [[Six-man tag team match]]\n|time7 = \n}}\n\n=== 2012 ===\nThe 2012 edition of the special was taped on December 9 at [[Norfolk Scope|The Scope]] in [[Norfolk, Virginia]], although referred to on-air as [[Naval Station Norfolk]]. [[USA Network]] aired a two-hour version of the show, which included all 5 matches, on December 19, while [[NBC]] aired a one-hour version three nights later, which included only the first and last match. The broadcast began with a pre-recorded message from President [[Barack Obama]], featured musical performances from [[Flo Rida]] and [[Kid Rock]], and a special Miz TV segment with [[Kermit the Frog]] and [[Miss Piggy]].\n\n{{Professional wrestling results table\n|results = \n|times = \n|hide = all\n\n|match1 = [[Randy Orton]] and [[Sheamus]] defeated [[Big Show]] and [[Dolph Ziggler]]\n|stip1 = [[Tag team match]]\n|time1 = \n\n|match2 = [[Ryback]] defeated [[Alberto Del Rio]] (with [[Ricardo Rodriguez (wrestler)|Ricardo Rodriguez]]) by [[disqualification (professional wrestling)|disqualification]]\n|stip2 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time2 = \n\n|match3 = [[The Miz]] defeated [[Damien Sandow]]\n|stip3 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time3 = \n\n|match4 = [[R-Truth]] and [[Team Hell No]] ([[Daniel Bryan]] and [[Kane (wrestler)|Kane]]) defeated 3MB ([[Heath Slater]], [[Drew McIntyre]] and [[Jinder Mahal]])\n|stip4 = [[Six-man tag team match]]\n|time4 = \n\n|match5 = [[John Cena]] defeated [[Antonio Cesaro]]\n|stip5 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time5 = \n}}\n\n=== 2013 ===\nThe 2013 edition of the special was taped on December 11 at the [[Joint Base Lewis-McChord]] in [[Tacoma, Washington]]. It aired December 28 on the [[NBC]]. The official theme songs for the event are \"Here's To Us\" by [[Kevin Rudolf]], \"People Back Home\" by [[Florida Georgia Line]] and \"[[Waiting for Superman (song)|Waiting For Superman]]\" by [[Daughtry (band)|Daughtry]]. Daughtry and [[Jeff Dunham]] performed, with the former ''[[SportsNation (TV series)|SportsNation]]'' host [[Michelle Beadle]] hosting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/inside/wwemusic/tribute-to-the-troops-music-2013-26170733|title= The music of WWE's Tribute to the Troops 2013|publisher=WWE|accessdate=2013-12-26}}</ref>\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|hide = all\n|results = <ref name=\"pwtorch.com\">{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwsuperstarsreport/article_75352.shtml|title=PWTorch.com - CALDWELL'S WWE TRIBUTE TO THE TROOPS REPORT 12/28: Complete \"virtual-time\" coverage of NBC special|website=pwtorch.com}}</ref>\n|times = <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=104967|title=WWE Tribute To The Troops 2013 \u00ab Events Database \u00ab CAGEMATCH - The Internet Wrestling Database|first=Philip|last=Kreikenbohm|website=www.cagematch.net}}</ref>\n|dark1 = yes\n|match1 = [[Big E Langston]] and [[Mark Henry]] defeated [[RybAxel]] ([[Ryback]] and [[Curtis Axel]])\n|stip1 = [[Tag team match]]\n|time1 = -\n|match2 = [[Daniel Bryan]] defeated [[Bray Wyatt]] (with [[Luke Harper]] and [[Erick Rowan]]) by [[disqualification (professional wrestling)|disqualification]]\n|stip2 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time2 = 1:43\n|match3 = [[CM Punk]] and [[Daniel Bryan]] defeated [[Luke Harper and Erick Rowan]] (with [[Bray Wyatt]]) by [[disqualification (professional wrestling)|disqualification]]\n|stip3 = [[Tag team match]]\n|time3 = 5:50\n|match4 = [[John Cena]], [[CM Punk]], and [[Daniel Bryan]] defeated [[The Wyatt Family]] ([[Bray Wyatt]], [[Luke Harper]], and [[Erick Rowan]])\n|stip4 = [[Six-man tag team match]]\n|time4 = 7:00\n|dark5 = yes\n|match5 = [[The Prime Time Players]] ([[Darren Young]] and [[Titus O'Neil]]) defeated 3MB ([[Drew McIntyre]] and [[Jinder Mahal]])\n|st